705707f-a.text:
24 Middagh Street, at the S.E. corner of Willow Street. This place was used as a Chop-house in 1815. Still standing in (1929).
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

705708f-a.text:
24-32 Middagh Street, south side, between Willow and Hicks Streets. TThe corner house was a chop house in 1815. It became a residence in 1838.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Arrbruster Collection.

707414f-a.text:
Willow Street, east side, at, adjoining and south of Middagh Street. Also seen are Nos. 24-26 Middagh Street, at and adjoining the S.E. corner of Willow Street. This cerner building (No. 24), was a chop house in 181. In 1836 it was the residence of Oliver Hutchinson. Iu 1922 a Mrs. Griswald
owned it.
April 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
